<MudDialog Class="dialog-card">
    <DialogContent>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6" Class="pb-6 header-primary" Style="font-weight: bold;">
            "I’m feeling quite hungry - for mods."
        </MudText>
        <MudText GutterBottom="true">
            A noble sentiment indeed.
        </MudText>
        <MudText GutterBottom="true">
            You've launched ModForge for the first time, which probably means you're ready to start shaping the world—or at least breaking it in style.
        </MudText>
        <MudText GutterBottom="true">
            But hold, noble tinkerer! Before we begin, there's one small issue: we're missing the sacred game data.
        </MudText>
        <MudText GutterBottom="true">
            Go to Settings, perform the ritual, and import the files. Only then shall the forge be lit.
        </MudText>
        <MudText GutterBottom="true" Style="font-style: italic">
            No data, no glory. No glory, no mods.
        </MudText>
        <MudText GutterBottom="true">
            Now set out on your path, and prove you’re more than just another drunk at the tavern bragging about “big plans.”
        </MudText>

    </DialogContent>
    <DialogActions>
        <MudButton Variant="Variant.Filled" Color="Color.Primary" OnClick="Submit">@ButtonText</MudButton>
    </DialogActions>
</MudDialog>